cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a method for generating realistic sequences of customer transactions using machine learning techniques such as Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN). This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG), as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) since the generated data can be used to gain insights into customer behavior. The paper also deals with customer and product databases, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses how the generated data can be used to better engage with customers, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
